1
00:00:10,219 --> 00:00:13,806
It was just after my daughter
Amy's third birthday.

2
00:00:13,973 --> 00:00:17,518
She ran up to me,
threw her arms around my legs,

3
00:00:17,685 --> 00:00:19,228
looked up and said...

4
00:00:19,228 --> 00:00:22,189
"Daddy, I've loved you
for four thousand years!"

5
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:24,316
I gazed into her little face.

6
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:27,361
A deep happiness enwrapped
my heart, body and soul.

7
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:28,696
Brian L. Weiss

8
00:00:42,918 --> 00:00:43,877
Toshiko...

9
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:46,839
Toshiko!

10
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:50,843
Want to drive!?

11
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:54,138
You got your license, right?

12
00:00:57,558 --> 00:00:59,018
Tomorrow you have to.

13
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:01,937
I'm quitting the hotel.

14
00:01:03,647 --> 00:01:04,773
You should, too...

15
00:01:06,150 --> 00:01:07,651
...when you've saved some money.

16
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:10,738
That guy's weird.

17
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:13,407
Original Story by
Minetaro Mochizuki

18
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:51,653
Is something wrong?

19
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:58,327
Could you check this again, please!?

20
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,330
I'll go make a call.

21
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:17,763
Hotel Symphonia...

22
00:02:22,059 --> 00:02:23,519
Your savings! Gone!

23
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:27,189
No, they're not gone.

24
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:30,651
I got a good stock tip,
so I invested them for you.

25
00:02:31,235 --> 00:02:33,946
You can't just take
someone's savings like that...

26
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:37,866
Hello?

27
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:39,743
Hello?

28
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:16,155
Hey, you!

29
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:25,164
Money, please.

30
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:27,875
Money, please.

31
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:30,210
Money, please.

32
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:58,859
Written and Directed by
Katsuhito Ishii

33
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:03,322
SHARK SKIN MAN
AND PEACH HIP GIRL

34
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:04,948
Two years later

35
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:10,162
My dad quit the mob,
but he couldn't quit the drugs.

36
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:14,875
With a regular job,
he had more money to buy them.

37
00:06:16,335 --> 00:06:18,712
He hid it from us,
but he was high all the time.

38
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:22,924
He got caught twice,
but he had the money for bail.

39
00:06:24,343 --> 00:06:28,513
Me and my mom and my brother
always used to say...

40
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:31,516
"Why don't you just stay in jail
for a while?"

41
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:37,022
He'd be eating ice cream
all the time.

42
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:39,358
You know, that white stuff...

43
00:06:39,941 --> 00:06:41,777
Like the ice shavings!?

44
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:45,447
Yeah, the stuff with that kind of
hard ice in it.

45
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:48,658
Our fridge was full of it.

46
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:50,744
I mean, obvious or what?

47
00:06:51,495 --> 00:06:54,956
When I was in middle school
I was sniffing glue in the living room...

48
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:58,919
...when the cops raided our house.
I ran upstairs...

49
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:03,298
...to hide my stuff in the closet.

50
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:08,220
But when I opened the closet,
all these bags of white powder...

51
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:11,932
...came falling out
where my dad had hidden them.

52
00:07:12,099 --> 00:07:13,892
I had it tough.

53
00:07:15,102 --> 00:07:18,313
When my old man was caught,
it was in the paper.

54
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:20,857
At school someone pasted the article
in the class paper.

55
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:24,778
People made fun of me,
and I hadn't done anything.

56
00:07:25,487 --> 00:07:27,614
Adults, too. Not just kids.

57
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:30,450
Adults made fun of you?

58
00:07:32,119 --> 00:07:35,580
We'd go to someone's house,
and I couldn't go in.

59
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:39,751
"Do you know what your dad did?"
their parents would say.

60
00:07:40,502 --> 00:07:44,798
"I didn't do it, you jerk!" I'd say.
"You know your son sniffs glue?"

61
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:48,885
When I see that in the papers,
I think of the kids...

62
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:52,264
They're the ones who suffer.

63
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:57,144
If kids came to my place,
they'd think the juice was spiked.

64
00:07:57,644 --> 00:08:00,605
As if you'd put speed
in orange juice!

65
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:06,611
When I was a kid,
I thought a tattoo...

66
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:10,365
...would appear on your back
when you grew up.

67
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,246
I really believed that!

68
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:15,472
What are you doing, Toshiko?
Did you sleep in?

69
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,017
Yes. I'm sorry.

70
00:09:21,061 --> 00:09:24,898
I stayed up reading...

71
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,401
Yes.

72
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:32,781
I'm sorry. I'll be right there.

73
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:37,369
What!

74
00:09:39,871 --> 00:09:40,872
Nothing.

75
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:44,334
You saw it, didn't you?

76
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,089
So what?

77
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:52,300
Nothing.

78
00:09:53,552 --> 00:09:54,719
It's enamel.

79
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:57,222
Enamel?

80
00:09:57,806 --> 00:09:59,641
Advertising posters like this.

81
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:01,851
They're called "enamel posters".

82
00:10:03,770 --> 00:10:06,189
You collect them?

83
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:09,276
- What's wrong with that?
- Nothing at all!

84
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:12,779
It's great.

85
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:16,908
I think they're very nice.

86
00:10:19,411 --> 00:10:22,247
You have to come way out here
in the country to find them.

87
00:10:22,497 --> 00:10:23,665
I know.

88
00:10:24,207 --> 00:10:26,751
You've got hobbies, don't you?

89
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,961
Yes!

90
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:31,256
If you see one of these, stop.

91
00:10:34,718 --> 00:10:36,553
Posters...

92
00:10:38,430 --> 00:10:40,181
- You are laughing at me...
- No, sir!

93
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:42,767
You think you can find them
anywhere, don't you.

94
00:10:43,852 --> 00:10:44,936
Don't you!

95
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:48,023
No...

96
00:10:48,565 --> 00:10:51,484
I think my grandmother
might have one...

97
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:53,486
What kind?

98
00:10:53,737 --> 00:10:57,574
An Ohmura Kon poster
for Oronamin C.

99
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:19,971
-You're...
- Sorry!

100
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,558
- What are you apologizing for?
- Nothing.

101
00:11:24,643 --> 00:11:27,520
There are about ten types
that I know of.

102
00:11:29,064 --> 00:11:30,899
The Ohmura Kon posters...

103
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:35,945
Are they the good ones!?

104
00:11:36,446 --> 00:11:37,989
This one's normal.

105
00:11:38,156 --> 00:11:42,952
The ones with "Golden Bat" or
"Attack Number I!" are rare.

106
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:46,039
Rare...

107
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:48,792
Rare.

108
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:52,981
Toshiko, where are you going?

109
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:54,566
Post office.

110
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:57,736
Say, "I'm going
to the post office."

111
00:12:58,403 --> 00:13:00,697
I'm going to the post office, Uncle.

112
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:02,657
Not "Uncle"...

113
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:04,784
Manager.

114
00:13:42,113 --> 00:13:43,573
Where's the guy who threw this?

115
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:49,496
Looks like he's gone.

116
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:52,415
- There were two girls there...
- Girls?

117
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,584
Is that all you think about?

118
00:13:54,876 --> 00:13:57,754
Why did Mr Tanuki go on ahead?

119
00:13:58,087 --> 00:14:00,131
Well, I don't know.

120
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,906
Just bump him, Sorimachi.

121
00:14:25,156 --> 00:14:28,076
May I! Die! Die!

122
00:14:28,243 --> 00:14:30,203
Sorimachi... he's getting away.

123
00:15:11,578 --> 00:15:13,413
It's freezing in here!

124
00:15:14,789 --> 00:15:17,250
Doesn't this damn heater work?

125
00:15:20,253 --> 00:15:22,046
Aren't you cold?!

126
00:15:30,513 --> 00:15:31,973
That's her phone...

127
00:15:45,737 --> 00:15:46,988
What the hell?

128
00:16:01,836 --> 00:16:02,879
Toshiko...

129
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,048
Are you at the post office yet?

130
00:16:19,896 --> 00:16:22,482
What's going on? Where are you?

131
00:16:22,774 --> 00:16:24,400
Get off my back!

132
00:16:27,278 --> 00:16:30,073
I cut him off...

133
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:54,389
Hotel Symphonia. Mail.

134
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:39,559
Are you all right?

135
00:17:40,685 --> 00:17:41,811
The poster.

136
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:46,816
Bring it.

137
00:18:09,464 --> 00:18:11,716
Why didn't you wait?

138
00:18:13,885 --> 00:18:15,261
What are you doing here?

139
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:18,681
The old man told me to come
if I wasn't doing anything.

140
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:22,643
Then do something! Well?

141
00:18:26,355 --> 00:18:27,440
Don't ignore me!

142
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:31,778
And... heave!

143
00:18:32,737 --> 00:18:33,946
Here's Tani...

144
00:19:24,789 --> 00:19:26,040
Excuse me...

145
00:19:28,084 --> 00:19:29,085
You still here?

146
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,678
Um... can I use the toilet?

147
00:20:21,971 --> 00:20:22,930
Please.

148
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:17,443
Sawada here...

149
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:34,687
You stink. Get out of here.

150
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,653
You stink! Get lost!

151
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,240
No!
Stop!

152
00:23:03,549 --> 00:23:05,217
Man, I'm lucky!

153
00:23:11,265 --> 00:23:12,683
This is a great jeep!

154
00:23:13,684 --> 00:23:15,269
Lovely. Well nice.

155
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:18,397
Really nice.

156
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:23,611
Come on! Mr Tanuki's gone in ahead.
He'll be mad again!

157
00:23:24,779 --> 00:23:26,864
So what? I like this jeep.

158
00:23:27,406 --> 00:23:28,491
Just come on.

159
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:31,535
You can drive it later. Let's go!

160
00:23:31,702 --> 00:23:32,953
Nice...

161
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:33,913
Well nice.

162
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,831
Tani-san, come on!

163
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:38,501
This is great!

164
00:23:38,709 --> 00:23:41,921
We're going! Come on, Tani-san!

165
00:23:42,296 --> 00:23:44,340
- Let's go!
- Nice.

166
00:23:44,507 --> 00:23:46,592
That guy pisses me off.

167
00:23:48,844 --> 00:23:51,680
What can you do!?
He's the boss's son.

168
00:23:51,889 --> 00:23:54,100
So why are we here!?

169
00:23:55,351 --> 00:23:57,645
Insurance. In case they need us.

170
00:23:58,437 --> 00:24:00,022
"Insurance"?!

171
00:24:49,572 --> 00:24:52,116
Didn't you teach Samehada anything?!

172
00:24:55,077 --> 00:24:56,120
Sorry...

173
00:24:56,704 --> 00:24:58,539
- Mitsuru...
- What!?

174
00:24:59,123 --> 00:25:00,791
You shouldn't talk like that.

175
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:02,084
Like what?

176
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:05,379
You don't tell people to stay back
just because they stink.

177
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:08,340
- Go to hell.
- You go to hell!

178
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,467
Sorimachi...

179
00:25:10,259 --> 00:25:11,385
Sorry.

180
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:14,638
Smell anything?

181
00:25:24,482 --> 00:25:25,691
Yep.

182
00:25:26,734 --> 00:25:29,945
Shampoo, rinse and
a woman on the rag.

183
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:43,042
You in there!?

184
00:25:44,043 --> 00:25:45,211
It's locked.

185
00:25:45,878 --> 00:25:47,171
Hold it here...

186
00:25:48,339 --> 00:25:49,465
No, here.

187
00:25:50,716 --> 00:25:51,675
Here?

188
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:08,984
What are you doing!?

189
00:26:09,985 --> 00:26:11,487
What are you doing!?

190
00:26:11,654 --> 00:26:15,199
Mitsuru says there should be
a smell from the ground.

191
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:17,576
Well, he's not
under the ground there!

192
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:18,827
I guess not.

193
00:26:22,456 --> 00:26:23,832
So what are you doing?

194
00:26:24,166 --> 00:26:25,793
- No, what are you doing?
- Over there.

195
00:26:27,086 --> 00:26:30,256
Turn your walkie-talkie on!

196
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:48,941
Get going.

197
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:51,986
Well?

198
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,322
- Hey!
- What?!

199
00:26:55,322 --> 00:26:57,241
- The woman!
- What about her?

200
00:27:09,878 --> 00:27:11,338
What happened here!?

201
00:27:16,176 --> 00:27:19,430
Out the back! Who said
go down in the basement?!

202
00:27:20,222 --> 00:27:21,599
You did!

203
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:27,938
What's the woman he's with like?

204
00:27:28,772 --> 00:27:29,898
I don't know.

205
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:32,943
I think you do...

206
00:27:35,738 --> 00:27:37,740
- What?
- Piss off!

207
00:27:45,748 --> 00:27:46,749
Asahina!

208
00:27:47,333 --> 00:27:48,751
Which way did he go?

209
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:51,420
I'll ask...

210
00:28:06,852 --> 00:28:09,229
- What?
- I got shot!

211
00:28:11,649 --> 00:28:13,525
Samehada's that way.

212
00:28:22,034 --> 00:28:23,285
Where's Samehada?

213
00:28:25,621 --> 00:28:26,789
Where's Samehada?!

214
00:28:53,982 --> 00:28:55,317
Can we go this way!?

215
00:28:56,819 --> 00:28:59,446
I came here when I was small.

216
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:05,763
Can you hear me?

217
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:07,389
Mitsuru, can you hear me?

218
00:30:08,432 --> 00:30:09,391
What!

219
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:11,351
You know what.

220
00:30:13,562 --> 00:30:15,022
Ah, Mr Tanuki...

221
00:30:17,107 --> 00:30:19,109
You know who it is.

222
00:30:19,568 --> 00:30:20,611
Idiot!

223
00:30:28,035 --> 00:30:29,203
What's going on?

224
00:30:30,788 --> 00:30:32,372
Who's an idiot?

225
00:30:33,165 --> 00:30:35,250
Don't talk to me like that.

226
00:30:35,959 --> 00:30:37,127
Where's Samehada?

227
00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:39,713
He's crossed the river.
I can't smell him.

228
00:30:40,464 --> 00:30:42,007
You can't smell him?

229
00:30:42,633 --> 00:30:46,220
He crossed with a woman.
Why can't you do that?

230
00:30:47,596 --> 00:30:48,889
I'll get wet!

231
00:30:50,891 --> 00:30:52,100
So what?

232
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:55,354
I hate water.

233
00:30:56,980 --> 00:31:00,442
You hate water? You're not a kid!

234
00:31:01,193 --> 00:31:03,821
I'm a kid with pubic hair.

235
00:31:05,364 --> 00:31:10,160
Pubic hair? We're not here
to talk about pubic hair.

236
00:31:11,411 --> 00:31:15,666
These clothes are bullet-proof.

237
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:20,754
It's not your regular leather.

238
00:31:21,421 --> 00:31:25,384
There's iron in them. If they
lose shape, it never comes back.

239
00:31:27,177 --> 00:31:28,512
What are you talking about?

240
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:31,265
Are you out of your mind?

241
00:31:33,141 --> 00:31:34,768
Are you out of your mind?

242
00:31:40,107 --> 00:31:41,650
Well? Are you?

243
00:31:48,657 --> 00:31:49,741
Samehada...

244
00:31:51,368 --> 00:31:52,411
The money...

245
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:54,621
Where's the money!?

246
00:31:55,497 --> 00:31:57,332
It's only 100 million yen!

247
00:31:58,625 --> 00:32:02,045
You know what happens
if you steal syndicate money?

248
00:32:03,046 --> 00:32:04,715
That's why I'm running.

249
00:32:05,132 --> 00:32:06,842
You think you can run?

250
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:09,595
Why do you think I'm running!?

251
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:12,014
Watch your mouth, son!

252
00:32:13,348 --> 00:32:14,766
Where's Sorimachi?

253
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:17,644
Why?

254
00:32:18,645 --> 00:32:20,230
I want to ask him something.

255
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:22,691
What!

256
00:32:23,609 --> 00:32:25,193
Not you, asshole!

257
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:27,237
Stop calling me that.

258
00:32:28,363 --> 00:32:29,740
Are you all listening?

259
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:32,659
Hey!

260
00:32:32,993 --> 00:32:35,120
- What?
- Do you all know?

261
00:32:36,371 --> 00:32:37,372
Know what?

262
00:32:38,206 --> 00:32:39,666
About your toupee!

263
00:32:40,334 --> 00:32:41,460
Samehada!!

264
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:49,718
This is starting to be fun!

265
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:52,054
Ow! Damn it!

266
00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:37,849
Why do you want to come
with me!?

267
00:33:39,768 --> 00:33:40,894
It's my birthday.

268
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,690
Today's my birthday.

269
00:33:46,733 --> 00:33:48,694
What's that got to do with me?

270
00:33:49,486 --> 00:33:50,946
I ran away.

271
00:34:03,208 --> 00:34:06,128
I don't know
what's going to happen...

272
00:34:35,282 --> 00:34:36,533
Hey, what's the matter?

273
00:34:39,578 --> 00:34:40,537
