01:03:54,623 --> 01:03:56,708
I can't do that.

550
01:03:57,959 --> 01:03:59,503
I can't do that to him.

551
01:03:59,753 --> 01:04:01,129
Yes, you can.

552
01:04:02,005 --> 01:04:03,757
I'll pay you like I said I would.

553
01:04:04,591 --> 01:04:05,926
You need money, don't you?

554
01:04:06,218 --> 01:04:08,220
You don't have any, do you...

555
01:04:18,313 --> 01:04:19,439
Is this OK?

556
01:04:19,731 --> 01:04:24,194
Yeah.
We can depend on this old guy.

557
01:04:26,863 --> 01:04:29,074
Whenever I need help,
I come to Shiota.

558
01:04:29,616 --> 01:04:30,784
It's fine.

559
01:04:34,746 --> 01:04:35,872
Just fine.

560
01:04:42,587 --> 01:04:43,588
Careful...

561
01:04:45,632 --> 01:04:46,842
What's this?

562
01:04:54,432 --> 01:04:55,600
We're here.

563
01:05:14,536 --> 01:05:16,580
This is a mess, Samehada.

564
01:05:17,539 --> 01:05:20,292
The whole syndicate is out
for your blood.

565
01:05:21,251 --> 01:05:22,752
It's fun, though.

566
01:05:23,336 --> 01:05:27,215
I'd like to try and
rip them off once, myself.

567
01:05:28,174 --> 01:05:30,260
Since the guys at the top
found out...

568
01:05:30,886 --> 01:05:32,888
...the old man with the wig
is in big trouble.

569
01:05:33,054 --> 01:05:34,180
Anyway...

570
01:05:34,347 --> 01:05:35,390
Who are you!?

571
01:05:39,269 --> 01:05:40,562
Momoijiri Toshiko.

572
01:05:40,729 --> 01:05:41,980
I don't mean your name.

573
01:05:41,980 --> 01:05:43,481
- She's with me.
- With you?

574
01:05:44,733 --> 01:05:45,692
I'm with him.

575
01:05:50,697 --> 01:05:51,698
Oh, man!

576
01:05:53,658 --> 01:05:56,536
Well, what should we do?

577
01:05:59,372 --> 01:06:01,958
First, get out of those
filthy clothes.

578
01:06:08,590 --> 01:06:09,883
That's a nice smile.

579
01:06:40,789 --> 01:06:42,165
What do you think?

580
01:07:02,894 --> 01:07:04,479
It's a bit cold, though.

581
01:07:15,824 --> 01:07:17,409
I liked the last one better, though.

582
01:07:29,629 --> 01:07:32,298
Tickets, maps, exchange rates,
everything.

583
01:07:33,008 --> 01:07:34,134
Do the contacts hurt!?

584
01:07:34,300 --> 01:07:35,343
They're fine.

585
01:07:35,969 --> 01:07:37,137
You're beautiful...

586
01:07:38,888 --> 01:07:43,768
That's sharkskin. One of a kind.

587
01:07:44,269 --> 01:07:45,895
Now, that's you!

588
01:07:47,022 --> 01:07:48,440
What do you think? Cool, huh?

589
01:07:49,232 --> 01:07:50,233
Super cool!

590
01:07:50,442 --> 01:07:51,943
Super cool!

591
01:07:53,987 --> 01:07:55,530
You're a great couple.

592
01:07:56,448 --> 01:07:57,574
We'd better hurry.

593
01:07:58,366 --> 01:07:59,325
Thanks.

594
01:08:00,410 --> 01:08:02,704
- What?
- The money, first.

595
01:08:02,954 --> 01:08:04,080
But I paid you...

596
01:08:04,664 --> 01:08:07,751
That's just for you.
You've got to pay for her. too.

597
01:08:08,960 --> 01:08:10,128
How much?

598
01:08:11,129 --> 01:08:12,380
Double.

599
01:08:12,630 --> 01:08:13,923
- Double?
- Double?

600
01:08:14,507 --> 01:08:16,593
It costs money to do up a woman.

601
01:08:20,263 --> 01:08:21,598
Listen, Samehada...

602
01:08:22,182 --> 01:08:25,685
...even I heard
you had a woman with you.

603
01:08:26,102 --> 01:08:29,230
That was a pretty dramatic escape,
but I'm on the line here, too.

604
01:08:30,982 --> 01:08:32,233
I'll send you the money.

605
01:08:32,233 --> 01:08:33,777
- Now.
- Now?

606
01:08:33,777 --> 01:08:36,654
- Now?
- Now. In cash.

607
01:08:37,197 --> 01:08:38,281
I can't!

608
01:08:38,281 --> 01:08:40,450
Well, forget it, then.

609
01:08:41,868 --> 01:08:43,286
Listen, Samehada...

610
01:08:45,288 --> 01:08:48,291
Your ass is on the line here,
but so is mine.

611
01:08:49,042 --> 01:08:52,629
What happens if they find out
I helped you?

612
01:08:53,296 --> 01:08:56,007
I've got to drop everything
and get out of here!

613
01:08:57,634 --> 01:08:59,219
The movers told me...

614
01:09:00,053 --> 01:09:02,680
...I've got too much stuff
and they can't take any chairs.

615
01:09:04,307 --> 01:09:07,185
I'm a chair collector!
Chairs are my life!

616
01:09:07,393 --> 01:09:08,770
Don't you understand?

617
01:09:09,270 --> 01:09:12,774
I'm going to leave them behind
and run! I'll need money!

618
01:09:13,441 --> 01:09:16,444
You understand that, don't you?
I'll need money!

619
01:09:20,073 --> 01:09:23,660
I'll be back in two hours.
You watch her.

620
01:10:09,914 --> 01:10:11,332
What are you doing!?

621
01:10:16,671 --> 01:10:17,964
What do you think?

622
01:10:18,423 --> 01:10:21,009
I think it's best
not to get involved.

623
01:10:21,176 --> 01:10:22,260
Why?

624
01:10:23,178 --> 01:10:26,431
Never get mixed up
in man-woman problems.

625
01:10:26,639 --> 01:10:27,640
Why not?

626
01:10:29,601 --> 01:10:31,978
My wife's just run off on me.

627
01:10:35,190 --> 01:10:38,234
With a young guy who came around
selling fire extinguishers.

628
01:10:42,906 --> 01:10:45,617
I'm sure
he was a good-looking guy.

629
01:10:47,744 --> 01:10:52,373
If he'd only been a jerk like you!
Then she wouldn't have gone.

630
01:11:53,184 --> 01:11:54,143
Yes.

631
01:11:57,605 --> 01:11:58,606
I'm sorry.

632
01:11:58,982 --> 01:12:01,317
I've got Samehada's girl.

633
01:12:02,944 --> 01:12:04,529
I should be there...

634
01:12:05,113 --> 01:12:07,865
...in about 90 minutes.

635
01:12:08,283 --> 01:12:09,325
Then...huh?

636
01:12:19,210 --> 01:12:20,420
Where's the girl?

637
01:12:22,839 --> 01:12:24,507
Sawada took her.

638
01:12:28,177 --> 01:12:29,345
Get out of here.

639
01:12:32,557 --> 01:12:34,392
Get going, now!

640
01:12:35,768 --> 01:12:39,814
I told him you'd be gone a while.
He believed me and took the girl.

641
01:12:53,661 --> 01:12:54,704
Where!?

642
01:12:56,456 --> 01:12:57,874
If 1 tell you, you'll follow him.

643
01:13:03,254 --> 01:13:05,548
OK, I did a deal with Sawada.
I'm sorry.

644
01:13:07,550 --> 01:13:09,135
But this saves your neck.

645
01:13:11,179 --> 01:13:12,555
You don't need to be like that.

646
01:13:17,101 --> 01:13:19,562
You don't even know her well.

647
01:13:21,606 --> 01:13:23,733
She doesn't mean anything to you.

648
01:13:25,026 --> 01:13:26,027
It's true!

649
01:14:05,274 --> 01:14:06,275
Sorry.

650
01:14:30,591 --> 01:14:31,759
An Oronamin C poster...

651
01:14:31,926 --> 01:14:33,845
...with a "Golden Bat"
or "Attack Number I!" on it...

652
01:14:33,845 --> 01:14:35,263
From a gum machine?

653
01:14:35,638 --> 01:14:37,765
- Yeah, a gum machine.
- One of those 20-yen prizes?

654
01:14:37,932 --> 01:14:39,934
Not those. They're 200 yen now.

655
01:14:40,101 --> 01:14:42,770
The Masked Rider figures.
They're great.

656
01:14:42,979 --> 01:14:45,481
What's the cop got to do with that?

657
01:14:45,857 --> 01:14:48,901
It's embarrassing, though,
being there with all those kids.

658
01:14:48,901 --> 01:14:50,153
What about the cop!?

659
01:14:50,528 --> 01:14:53,364
There was this guy
always hanging around the arcade.

660
01:14:53,531 --> 01:14:54,824
And he was a cop!?

661
01:14:54,824 --> 01:14:57,243
Yeah. I figured him
for some kind of weirdo...

662
01:14:57,577 --> 01:14:59,871
...but then I found out
he collected these things too.

663
01:14:59,871 --> 01:15:01,622
We started trading,
like, at McDonalds...

664
01:15:01,914 --> 01:15:03,791
...Then I found out.
He's the guy who told me.

665
01:15:03,958 --> 01:15:04,917
"Yoga Friend"...

666
01:15:05,501 --> 01:15:06,669
"Yoga Friend"?

667
01:15:07,003 --> 01:15:08,671
The book next to the body.

668
01:15:09,505 --> 01:15:10,756
That was "Yoga Castle".

669
01:15:10,965 --> 01:15:12,967
"Castle"? Like in "castle"?

670
01:15:13,384 --> 01:15:14,385
Yeah.

671
01:15:15,178 --> 01:15:16,387
Where can we get it!

672
01:15:42,705 --> 01:15:43,789
Shit!

673
01:16:12,360 --> 01:16:13,528
Are you OK?

674
01:16:15,571 --> 01:16:17,031
I can't do it. Damn!

675
01:17:22,138 --> 01:17:23,723
Sawada? Sawada!?

676
01:17:23,973 --> 01:17:25,933
Don't you even know
who Sawada is!?

677
01:17:25,933 --> 01:17:27,435
Fuka-chan...

678
01:17:27,727 --> 01:17:28,894
Who's Fuka-chan?

679
01:17:29,228 --> 01:17:31,689
- Huh?
- He was Samehada's buddy!

680
01:17:51,292 --> 01:17:53,044
What did he say?

681
01:17:55,379 --> 01:17:59,508
I just got shit because
you and Sawada were buddies!

682
01:18:02,595 --> 01:18:04,180
Where is Mr Sawada?

683
01:18:05,431 --> 01:18:06,891
He disappeared.

684
01:18:09,226 --> 01:18:10,936
Maybe he's hiding somewhere...

685
01:18:17,652 --> 01:18:18,736
Hey!

686
01:18:18,736 --> 01:18:19,737
Gonna piss.

687
01:18:20,655 --> 01:18:23,407
Watch your manners
or I'll get mad!

688
01:18:24,492 --> 01:18:26,243
I don't want to go inside.

689
01:18:53,604 --> 01:18:55,773
Where's the girl?

690
01:18:58,275 --> 01:18:59,568
Where is she?

691
01:19:00,111 --> 01:19:01,195
Don't shoot!

692
01:19:02,154 --> 01:19:03,406
Where is she?!

693
01:19:04,448 --> 01:19:07,493
She and Sawada disappeared.

694
01:19:13,999 --> 01:19:15,042
Where's the money!?

695
01:20:06,719 --> 01:20:08,220
Toshiko! I've been worried!

696
01:20:12,099 --> 01:20:13,476
Samehada!

697
01:20:14,477 --> 01:20:15,770
Samehada!

698
01:20:26,238 --> 01:20:27,198
Yamada...

699
01:20:28,449 --> 01:20:29,450
Yamada!

700
01:20:34,330 --> 01:20:35,372
You can go.

701
01:20:36,040 --> 01:20:36,999
Go.

702
01:20:39,794 --> 01:20:40,836
I hate you.

703
01:20:41,670 --> 01:20:44,256
You've got to work
tomorrow morning. Go home.

704
01:20:44,965 --> 01:20:46,133
Go home, damn it!

705
01:20:49,512 --> 01:20:51,472
My bank account...

706
01:20:52,014 --> 01:20:54,225
I know that, damn it! Go home!

707
01:20:54,725 --> 01:20:55,768
Go home, I said!

708
01:21:01,857 --> 01:21:03,442
Go home! Get lost!

709
01:21:07,112 --> 01:21:08,531
Scram you idiot.

710
01:21:15,287 --> 01:21:16,622
Let's go somewhere.

711
01:21:17,039 --> 01:21:19,542
I know where we can go.

712
01:22:22,897 --> 01:22:24,315
He's out cold.

713
01:22:27,568 --> 01:22:28,527
Chair.

714
01:22:31,405 --> 01:22:32,406
Chair.

715
01:22:46,337 --> 01:22:47,504
Not for you.

716
01:23:13,364 --> 01:23:16,450
If you don't talk, you die.

717
01:23:18,243 --> 01:23:23,374
Mr Tanuki... there's no money
in his briefcase.

718
01:23:27,169 --> 01:23:28,337
Samehada...

719
01:23:30,965 --> 01:23:32,091
Samehada...

720
01:23:35,302 --> 01:23:36,387
The bat.

721
01:23:51,235 --> 01:23:52,236
Sis...

722
01:23:54,238 --> 01:23:56,407
I'll be in my room.

723
01:24:01,412 --> 01:24:02,371
The bat.

724
01:24:38,741 --> 01:24:40,075
Would you like some coffee?

725
01:24:40,784 --> 01:24:42,119
Yeah, good idea...

726
01:25:47,810 --> 01:25:51,563
This happened before...
when I was young.

727
01:25:51,563 --> 01:25:54,733
A silly woman ran out on me.

728
01:25:55,275 --> 01:25:56,401
Keep still...

729
01:25:58,112 --> 01:25:59,738
We'll be married, soon.

730
01:26:01,490 --> 01:26:02,825
Keep still, I said!

731
01:26:10,999 --> 01:26:12,459
Keep still, you idiot!

732
01:26:26,849 --> 01:26:27,891
Keep still!

733
01:27:18,567 --> 01:27:19,526
Huh?

734
01:28:03,195 --> 01:28:04,196
Shit!

735
01:28:33,809 --> 01:28:36,103
What are those bastards doing
in my hotel?!

736
01:28:36,728 --> 01:28:38,814
Don't move! I'll spank you!

737
01:28:40,357 --> 01:28:41,900
Let me get a flashlight...

738
01:28:42,943 --> 01:28:44,152
Don't move, I said!

739
01:28:46,488 --> 01:28:48,282
Don't touch me, you pervert!

740
01:28:48,282 --> 01:28:50,033
What!

741
01:28:53,620 --> 01:28:55,789
Yeah, like that. Keep still.

742
01:28:57,833 --> 01:28:58,959
Don't move.

743
01:31:06,920 --> 01:31:08,380
An ambulance...

744
01:31:12,551 --> 01:31:14,970
Call an ambulance, please.

745
01:34:56,816 --> 01:34:58,401
This is good-bye, Samehada.

746
01:35:03,239 --> 01:35:08,328
If you'd followed Sorimachi's plan
and took the money together...

747
01:35:10,163 --> 01:35:12,957
...none of this would have happened.

748
01:35:16,044 --> 01:35:18,421
The money was supposed
to come to me.

749
01:35:22,634 --> 01:35:24,010
Where is it?

750
01:35:35,605 --> 01:35:36,815
What's so funny?

751
01:35:39,901 --> 01:35:41,319
Your face.

752
01:35:47,909 --> 01:35:49,077
Drop the gun.

753
01:36:00,255 --> 01:36:01,506
Drop the gun!

754
01:36:06,136 --> 01:36:08,096
Don't try anything stupid, Tanuki.

755
01:36:10,181 --> 01:36:11,391
Don't you either.

756
01:37:00,273 --> 01:37:02,942
Get away from her, Four-eyes!

757
01:37:03,735 --> 01:37:04,736
"Four-eyes"?

758
01:37:05,737 --> 01:37:06,696
Samehada!

759
01:37:44,275 --> 01:37:45,401
Samehada!

760
01:37:46,528 --> 01:37:47,654
Samehada!

761
01:37:49,072 --> 01:37:50,240
Samehada!

762
01:38:21,396 --> 01:38:22,856
I remember now...

763
01:38:24,399 --> 01:38:25,650
Money, please.

764
01:38:27,610 --> 01:38:28,945
Money, please.

765
01:38:31,155 --> 01:38:32,448
Money, please.

766
01:38:38,246 --> 01:38:41,791
Someone call an ambulance, please!

767
01:38:44,794 --> 01:38:46,129
Don't move, please.

768
01:38:48,172 --> 01:38:49,424
Don't move, please.

769
01:38:51,467 --> 01:38:52,468
But...

770
01:38:54,012 --> 01:38:55,471
Don't move, please.

771
01:38:56,431 --> 01:38:57,640
Don't move, please.

772
01:39:07,150 --> 01:39:08,526
A little more, please.

773
01:39:09,485 --> 01:39:10,820
A little more, please.

774
01:39:15,199 --> 01:39:16,868
There should still be more.

775
01:39:51,069 --> 01:39:52,654
Thank you very much.

776
01:39:54,989 --> 01:39:56,616
Thank you very much.

777
01:40:54,215 --> 01:40:55,341
This is it?

778
01:41:01,097 --> 01:41:03,725
Sawada and God

779
01:41:04,809 --> 01:41:06,602
I keep having this dream...

780
01:41:11,816 --> 01:41:16,946
They sit me in this chair.
In front if me is God, talking.

781
01:41:18,906 --> 01:41:20,074
God?

782
01:41:21,159 --> 01:41:22,660
I think that's what it was.

783
01:41:24,454 --> 01:41:25,580
You believe in God?

784
01:41:28,124 --> 01:41:29,083
Yeah.

785
01:41:36,507 --> 01:41:40,470
"Help them both",
he keeps repeating.

786
01:41:42,388 --> 01:41:44,682
"Help them both"?

787
01:41:44,932 --> 01:41:51,898
Yeah. I wonder if that means
you and Samehada...

788
01:42:01,574 --> 01:42:04,118
- Um...
- You can run if you want.

789
01:42:10,583 --> 01:42:11,834
Now's the chance.

790
01:42:13,961 --> 01:42:15,671
I'm not cut out for this job.

791
01:42:20,051 --> 01:42:21,719
It's a good chance to get out.

792
01:42:27,266 --> 01:42:28,559
So get going.

793
01:43:21,946 --> 01:43:22,905
Thanks.

794
